# TypeScript build (lib)

**Entry points** (scripts loaded by HTML): `lib/page/*.ts` and `lib/common/*.ts`. After editing any of these or any `.ts` they import (e.g. under `lib/tsl/`), run the build so the browser gets updated code:

From project root:
```bash
cd lib && npm run build
```

Or: `node lib/build.js` from project root.

This uses **esbuild** to bundle each entry; output stays alongside source (`lib/page/*.js`, `lib/common/*.js`). **Imports in TS can be extensionless** (e.g. `from "../tsl/visual"` instead of `from "../tsl/visual.js"`); the bundler resolves them.

**Single file not used in HTML** (e.g. `lib/test/test_math.ts`): you can still compile with tsc if you need a standalone .js:

From project root:
```bash
cd lib && npx tsc test/test_math.ts --esModuleInterop --target es2019 --module esnext --skipLibCheck --strict
```

Do not use `--outDir` so the .js is emitted next to the .ts.
